{
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionIt is a stereotypical epigram among the research community to present Artificial Intelligence (AI) as the simulation of Natural Intelligence (NI), in reference to a set of processes performed by computers to mirror as close as possible the functions of the human brain.",
    "These processes include primarily the acquisition of information via a process called Machine Learning (ML) and specific rules for deriving and using the information within.",
    "Then, secondary reasoning, using a set of rules to reach approximate or definite conclusions, and finally, a process of self-correction [1].",
    "However, everything begins with a human command.",
    "On the other hand, Natural Intelligence is considered as the innate ability of living organisms, more particularly humans, to learn, feel, understand, adapt, and make decisions based on their environment."
  ]
}